1.  docker network create myapp-network

2. docker run -d --rm --name mongo --network myapp-network -v data:/data/db mongo



docker build -t myimage .
docker run -p 3000:7000 --name myapp -v myvolume:/app/perm -v /app/node_modules -v "C:\Users\miste\OneDrive\Documents\docker\chap06:/app" --env-file ./.env --network myapp-network myimage

docker stop mongo myapp




-------------
Point to remember -
		 1. You can use Docker compose for one or more appliction/Container.
		 2. Docker compose is not replacing dockerfiles. 
		 3. Docker compose is for one machine only, one one machine you can create multi Contain. 

